🧠 3548. Equal Sum Grid Partition II — Notes
🔹 Core Intuition

We need to check:

👉 Can we make 1 cut (horizontal OR vertical) such that:

Two parts have equal sum
OR can be made equal by removing at most 1 cell
AND after removal → section must remain connected
🔥 Key Observations
1. Total Sum Split

Let:

top = sum of upper part
bottom = total - top

We want:

top == bottom
OR
|top - bottom| == value of some cell (removable)
2. Only ONE cell can be removed

So difference must match exactly one cell value:

diff = top - bottom

Cases:

diff == 0 → ✅ valid
diff > 0 → remove from TOP
diff < 0 → remove from BOTTOM
3. Connectivity Constraint ⚠️ (MOST IMPORTANT)

You CANNOT remove arbitrary cell

Removing a cell should NOT break the section into 2 parts.

👉 So which cells are safe?

Border cells (edges)
Or cells that don’t disconnect region

💡 Your trick:
Instead of explicitly checking connectivity →
you restrict removal to valid positions implicitly

⚡ Your Smart Trick (Important)
You maintain:
unordered_set<ll> st;

This stores values of top section

Then:

if(st.count(diff)) → valid removal

But only when:

i > 0 && n > 1

👉 This avoids edge-disconnection issues.

🔁 Why reverse(grid)?

This is GENIUS 🔥

Problem:

You only check removal from TOP section

But what if removal needed from BOTTOM?

Solution:

Instead of writing separate logic:

👉 You simply:

reverse(grid)

Now:

Bottom becomes top
Same logic works
So effectively:
Original	After reverse
Remove from top	Remove from bottom
🔄 Why Transpose?

We also need vertical cuts

Instead of writing new logic:

👉 Convert:

columns → rows
transposeGrid[j][i] = grid[i][j];

Now:

Vertical cut becomes horizontal cut
🧩 Full Approach
Step 1: Compute total sum
total = sum of grid
Step 2: Try all horizontal cuts
checkHorCuts(grid)
Step 3: Reverse grid (handle bottom removal)
reverse(grid)
checkHorCuts(grid)
Step 4: Transpose → handle vertical cuts
transposeGrid
checkHorCuts(transposeGrid)
Step 5: Reverse transpose
reverse(transposeGrid)
checkHorCuts(transposeGrid)
🧠 checkHorCuts() Logic
for each row cut i:
    add row to top sum
    store elements in set

    bottom = total - top
    diff = top - bottom

    if diff == 0 → return true

    if diff matches some valid removable cell → return true
⚠️ Special Edge Handling (Important)
if (diff == grid[0][0])   return true;
if (diff == grid[0][n-1]) return true;
if (diff == grid[i][0])   return true;

👉 These handle boundary cases where:

removing corner cells is always safe (no disconnection)
🧮 Time Complexity
Each pass: O(m × n)
Total passes: ~4

👉 Final:

O(m × n)
